body:
Hi [Name],

Thank you for bringing the authentication issue to our attention. I've investigated the problem and gathered the relevant error logs and code snippets that should help us resolve this quickly.

**Error Logs:**
```
[2024-01-15 14:23:45] ERROR: Authentication failed for user@example.com
[2024-01-15 14:23:45] AuthenticationException: Invalid token signature
[2024-01-15 14:23:45] Stack trace: at TokenValidator.verify() line 127
[2024-01-15 14:23:45] Token expiration: 2024-01-15 14:20:00 (expired 3m 45s ago)
```

**Relevant Code Snippet:**
```javascript
// Current authentication flow (line 124-135)
async function validateUserToken(token) {
  try {
    const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET);
    const user = await User.findById(decoded.userId);

    if (!user || user.tokenVersion !== decoded.tokenVersion) {
      throw new AuthenticationException('Invalid token signature');
    }
    return user;
  } catch (error) {
    logger.error('Authentication failed:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}
```

**Identified Issues:**
1. Token expiration time is set to 3 minutes (should be 30 minutes)
2. Token version mismatch occurring during password resets
3. JWT_SECRET environment variable may not be synced across all instances

**Proposed Solution:**
I recommend updating the token expiration configuration and implementing a grace period for token version transitions. I can provide the updated code if you'd like to proceed with this approach.

Please let me know if you need any additional information or if you'd like to schedule a quick call to discuss the implementation. I'm happy to help resolve this as soon as possible.

Best regards,
[Your Name]
[Your Title]
[Contact Information]

# HTML Email: Tupperware Set Dispatch Confirmation

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
